The Governor shall appoint a Bicycle and Pedestrian Advisory Committee to provide guidance to State agencies concerning:
Funding of bicycle and pedestrian related programs;
Public education and awareness of bicycling and pedestrian related activities;
Public education and awareness of bicycling and pedestrian safety; and
Any other issue directly related to bicycling and pedestrians.

The Committee shall consist of the following:
One representative each from:
The Department of Transportation;
The Department of Natural Resources;
The State Department of Education;
The Department of State Police;
The Department of Business and Economic Development;
The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene;
The Department of Planning;
The Department of Disabilities; and
The Maryland-National Capital Park and Planning Commission;
One citizen member from each of the following areas:
The Eastern Shore;
Western Maryland; and
Southern Maryland;
Two citizen members from each of the following areas:
The Baltimore metropolitan area; and
The Washington metropolitan area; and
Up to six citizen members selected to represent the interests of bicyclists, pedestrians, and the disabled community to include:
A representative of individuals who are visually impaired; and
A representative of individuals who are mobility impaired.
